.TH "port_cfg_shift" 9 "port_cfg_shift" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
port_cfg_shift \- set port bit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" port_cfg_shift
.BI "(struct ksz_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "int port "  ","
.BI "u32 addr "  ","
.BI "int shift "  ","
.BI "int set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The hardware instance.
.IP "port" 12
The port index.
.IP "addr" 12
The offset of the register.
.IP "shift" 12
Number of bits to shift.
.IP "set" 12
The flag indicating whether the port is to be set or not.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine sets or resets the specified port in the register.
